cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper presents an information-theoretic formulation of the problem and proposes a coding scheme to achieve the secrecy capacity region of the channel. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper deals with the problem of secure communication and proposes a coding scheme to embed a high-security message into a low-security message. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper may be relevant to the study of secure communication in social networks or other information networks. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to the study of secure communication of multimedia data. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve some computational complexity analysis of the proposed coding scheme.
